Title : Bilateral congenital dislocation of the patella.
Date : 1996
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : We report the case of a six-year-old boy with Down syndrome who presented with flexion contractures of both knees and genu valgum. The diagnosis of bilateral congenital dislocation of the patella was established by clinical and xray examination. The patient was treated surgically with a satisfactory result.
